    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 997.1 Carrera S, a masterpiece of analog engineering. This specimen is powered by the 3.8L M97 flat-six, mated to a crisp 6-speed manual gearbox with a factory short-shift kit. The vehicle features Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and a limited-slip differential for superior corner-exit traction. Maintenance is exhaustive: the IMS bearing has been proactively upgraded to a ceramic dual-row solution, and the cooling system has been refreshed with a low-temp thermostat. The paint is entirely original, exhibiting deep luster and zero imperfections. Mechanically, the engine demonstrates perfect compression across all cylinders with no signs of bore scoring. A rare find for the discerning collector seeking peak mechanical performance and a pristine chassis.",
